<br>
It would be self defense in this case. FFS he has an invading army on his borders who has clearly stated that they have every intention of invading and occupying his country. WTF would you do? Sit and wait idly by for the hammer to fall? I am damn sure the US wouldn't play it that way, but we expect him to just give up. <br>
<br>
This crisis situation was created by us. We are making all the threats, we are making all the hostile moves. You can use missiles that go 19 miles over a limit or drone planes as justification, but it doesn't change the fact that WE are the agressor in this particular situation. Are you going to sit there and tell me that if Suddam attacks us today that it is not self defense? Whether you like him or not, whether you believe he should be removed or not, the fact is that WE are the agressors and that means that we are open to all the repercussions that can result from that.<br>
<br>
So yes, if he attacked our soldiers and invaded Kuwait, it would be 100% Bush fault. Suddam was no threat to us until we moved on him. Now he will do what he has to to defend his country, just like we would. And don't give me this BS about we wouldn't have been in this situation because we would have complied with the UN, because it is clear we have -0- respect for the UN, yet we expect Saddam to.<br>
<br>
We talk the talk, but we don't walk the walk when we say what other countries should do. We say we have the right to invade Iraq because they didn't follow a UN resolution, yet if the UN vetos us we have stated we will invade Iraq anyway. Funny how it all depends on who it is whether the UN's will should be followed or not.<br>
<br>
I'll say it again - I have no love for Saddam, but I also know BS when I smell it, and we are shoveling it by the truckload on this one.<br>
<br>
